"title": "5804: charm",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5804: charm",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The gracious effect of attracting and captivating others or the subtle ability to deceive and mislead them.</p>\n<h2>Charm to attract and captivate others</h2>\n<h3>King Xerxes by Esther</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth2:17\">EST 2:17</a></p>\n<h3>A husband by his wife</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov5:18-Prov5:19\">PRO 5:18–5:19</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The lovers in the Song of Solomon</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song1:15-Song1:16\">SNG 1:15–1:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song2:14\">SNG 2:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:9-Song4:10\">SNG 4:9–4:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song5:16\">SNG 5:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song6:4-Song6:5\">SNG 6:4–6:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song7:6\">SNG 7:6</a></p>\n<h2>Charm to deceive people</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov26:24-Prov26:25\">PRO 26:24–26:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:25-Prov6:26\">PRO 6:25–6:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:30\">PRO 31:30</a></p>\n<h3>The devil subtly seeks to deceive people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:3\">2CO 11:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:14\">2CO 11:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:1-Gen3:5\">GEN 3:1–3:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:13\">GEN 3:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:1-Matt4:11\">MAT 4:1–4:11</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:12-Mark1:13\">MRK 1:12–1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:1-Luke4:13\">LUK 4:1–4:13</a></p>\n<h3>Absalom deceived others</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:1-2Sam15:6\">2SA 15:1–15:6</a></p>\n<h2>False teachers use charm to deceive others</h2>\n<h3>For their own gain</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:18\">ROM 16:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:16\">JUD 1:16</a></p>\n<h3>To draw people away from Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:18\">2PE 2:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor11:13-2Cor11:15\">2CO 11:13–11:15</a></p>\n<h3>Christians must not be deceived by such charm</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:14\">EPH 4:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:6\">EPH 5:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:4\">COL 2:4</a></p>",
